## MODEL DDL Syntax

Every SQLMesh SQL model file contains a `MODEL` DDL block followed by the query:

```sql
MODEL (
  name catalog.schema.model_name,       -- fully qualified name (required)
  kind FULL,                             -- model kind (required)
  owner 'team@company.com',             -- owner (WARN if missing)
  cron '@daily',                         -- schedule (optional)
  grain (id, event_date),               -- unique key for INCREMENTAL models (required for INCREMENTAL_BY_UNIQUE_KEY)
  partitioned_by (event_date),          -- partition columns (optional, recommended for large tables)
  tags (finance, critical),             -- classification tags (optional)
  audits (UNIQUE_VALUES(columns=(id)), NOT_NULL(columns=(id))),  -- built-in audits
  depends_on (catalog.schema.other_model),  -- explicit deps (auto-detected from SQL, use only for overrides)
);

SELECT
  id::BIGINT,
  lower(email)::TEXT         AS email,
  created_at::TIMESTAMP      AS created_at,
  current_timestamp()        AS _loaded_at
FROM catalog.raw.source_table
```

---

## Model Kinds

| Kind | IronLayer Mapping | Use Case |
|------|-----------------|----------|
| `FULL` | FULL_REFRESH / TABLE | Small reference tables, dimensions that change rarely |
| `VIEW` | FULL_REFRESH / VIEW | Logical layer, no storage cost |
| `INCREMENTAL_BY_TIME_RANGE` | INCREMENTAL_BY_TIME_RANGE / INSERT_OVERWRITE | Event/fact tables partitioned by time; requires `time_column` |
| `INCREMENTAL_BY_UNIQUE_KEY` | MERGE_BY_KEY / MERGE | Dimension-like tables with a stable unique key; requires `grain` |
| `INCREMENTAL_BY_PARTITION` | INCREMENTAL_BY_TIME_RANGE / INSERT_OVERWRITE | Partition-based incremental without time column |
| `SCD_TYPE_2` | MERGE_BY_KEY / MERGE | Slowly Changing Dimensions with history tracking |
| `SEED` | FULL_REFRESH / TABLE | Static seed/lookup data |
| `EMBEDDED` | FULL_REFRESH / VIEW | CTE-like ephemeral model (no physical table) |

### BLOCK if:
- `INCREMENTAL_BY_UNIQUE_KEY` model has no `grain` defined
- `INCREMENTAL_BY_TIME_RANGE` model has no `time_column` defined
- `FULL` model on a source table known to exceed 1B rows without partitioning

### WARN if:
- MODEL block is missing `owner`
- `INCREMENTAL_BY_UNIQUE_KEY` model has `grain` but no `partitioned_by` for large tables (> 10M rows estimated)
- Model name does not follow the catalog.schema.name fully-qualified convention

