## Naming Conventions

SQLMesh models use fully-qualified names in the MODEL DDL:

```sql
MODEL (
  name prod_catalog.gold.fct_orders,   -- catalog.schema.model_name
  ...
);
```

Exodus naming conventions within SQLMesh:
- Staging: `{client}_raw.staging.stg_{source}__{table}` — 1:1 source, VIEW kind
- Intermediate: `{client}_prod.silver.int_{domain}__{desc}` — business logic, TABLE kind
- Dimensions: `{client}_prod.gold.dim_{entity}` — SCD or FULL kind
- Facts: `{client}_prod.gold.fct_{event}` — INCREMENTAL_BY_TIME_RANGE kind

Note: SQLMesh resolves environments via Virtual Data Environments (pointer swaps on views), so the physical table names include an `_{environment}` suffix in dev/CI environments. In production, names resolve to the catalog.schema.model without suffix.

