## Review Checklist for SQLMesh PRs

When reviewing a PR with SQLMesh changes:

- [ ] MODEL block is present and well-formed (no missing required attributes)
- [ ] `name` is fully qualified: `catalog.schema.model_name`
- [ ] `owner` is set
- [ ] INCREMENTAL models have `grain` (INCREMENTAL_BY_UNIQUE_KEY) or `time_column` (INCREMENTAL_BY_TIME_RANGE)
- [ ] At minimum, `UNIQUE_VALUES` and `NOT_NULL` audits on grain columns
- [ ] No hardcoded `database.schema.table` references — use `ref()` equivalent (other model names in FROM clause, SQLMesh resolves them)
- [ ] No `SELECT *` in production models (breaks column-level lineage)
- [ ] Python macros are defined in `macros/` directory, not inline
- [ ] Blueprint templates resolve to valid model names (no special characters)
- [ ] Unit test file exists in `tests/` for any model containing non-trivial business logic
